# How do the focused and diffuse thinking modes relate to our ability to learn and solve problems?

It is important that you are able to switch between the two modes of thinking in order to learn and solve problems. Analagous to physical exercise, you need periods of stimulation (focused mode) and periods of rest (diffuse mode) in order for new ideas to embed themselves in your mind.

